'''Budapest Spring Festival''' ([[Hungarian language|Hungarian]]: ''Budapesti Tavaszi Fesztivál'') is the major [[arts festival]] of [[Budapest]], [[Hungary]],<ref>{{cite web| url=http://visitbudapest.travel/budapest-events/budapest-spring-festival/ | title=Budapest Spring Festival | publisher= Visit Budapest | accessdate=1 August 2014 }}</ref> sponsored by the city government.{{fact|date=August 2014}}

The festival is focused on traditional arts, and is larger than its sister event the [[Budapest Autumn Festival]], which is primarily for modern and avant garde performances.<ref>{{cite book| title=Budapest | publisher=[[Lonely Planet]] | year=2012 }}</ref>

